2026-03-11 | Sum of Subarray Minimums

	Question
Return the total sum of minimum elements across all subarrays.

	Approach
1.	Instead of generating all subarrays, compute contribution of each element.
2.	For arr[i], find:
		left = distance to previous smaller element
		right = distance to next smaller element
3.	arr[i] will be the minimum for:
		left × right subarrays
4.	Contribution:
		arr[i] × left × right
5.	Use two monotonic stacks to compute:
		previous smaller element
		next smaller element
6.	Sum all contributions.

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(n)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int sumSubarrayMins(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        vector<int> left(n), right(n);
        stack<int> st;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            while (!st.empty() && arr[st.top()] > arr[i])
                st.pop();

            left[i] = st.empty() ? (i + 1) : (i - st.top());
            st.push(i);
        }

        while (!st.empty()) st.pop();

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            while (!st.empty() && arr[st.top()] >= arr[i])
                st.pop();

            right[i] = st.empty() ? (n - i) : (st.top() - i);
            st.push(i);
        }

        long long ans = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
            ans += (long long)arr[i] * left[i] * right[i];

        return ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Each element contributes to several subarrays as the minimum.  
By determining how far it can extend left and right before encountering a smaller value,  
we can compute its total contribution efficiently in **O(n)** time.
